{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_102","type":"agent_message","text":"The diagnosis points to the condition phase, not the property phase: `HttpServiceClientProperties` is bound correctly, but `WebClientHttpServiceGroupConfigurer` beans are completely absent in native mode. The most plausible missing piece is `HttpServiceProxyRegistryFactoryBean.getObjectType()`, which `@ConditionalOnBean(HttpServiceProxyRegistry.class)` can use while deciding whether to activate `ReactiveHttpServiceClientAutoConfiguration`. I’m adding that method to the existing factory-bean reflection entry next."}}
